 Gold | 5,250 | Gold ETF / Fund SIP |\n| Crypto | 3,500 | BTC/ETH |\n| **Total Allocated** | **\u20b934,000** | |\n\n---\n\n### 5) Risks, Assumptions, and Mitigation\n\n*   **Risks:**\n    *   **Market Volatility:** Your bike and wealth-building investments are subject to market falls, especially the crypto portion.\n    *   **Inflation:** The cost of your goals (Bike, iPhone) may increase in 1-2 years.\n    *   **Income Shock:** Job loss or medical emergency could disrupt the plan.\n*   **Assumptions:**\n    *   Your income and expenses remain stable for the next two years.\n    *   You do not acquire any new debt.\n    *   You will not dip into the invested funds for impulsive purchases.\n*   **Mitigation:**\n    *   The **Emergency Fund** is your first defense against income shocks.\n    *   The Balanced Advantage Fund for the bike goal automatically reduces equity exposure if markets become expensive, mitigating downside risk.\n    *   By investing slightly more than the bare minimum for your bike (\u20b99,000 vs. \u20b98,333), you create a buffer against minor cost inflation.\n    *   **Do not increase your lifestyle expenses** as your salary grows. Channel any future increments directly into your investments.\n\n---\n\n### 6) Immediate Action Checklist (Next 7 Days)\n\n1.  [ ] **Open New Bank Accounts:** Create two separate savings accounts: one labeled \"EMERGENCY FUND\" and another \"GOALS.\"\n2.  [ ] **Initiate Emergency Fund:** Transfer **\u20b910,000** to your \"EMERGENCY FUND\" account. Set up a auto-transfer of \u20b910,000 for the next 4 months.\n3.  [ ] **Select Financial Products:**\n    *   Research and select one **Liquid Fund** for your emergency fund.\n    *   Research and select one **Debt Fund** or set up an **RD** for your iPhone goal.\n    *   Research and select one **Balanced Advantage Fund** for your bike goal.\n4.  [ ] **Create Investment Accounts:** Open accounts with a reputable mutual fund platform (e.g., Coin, Groww, Zerodha) and a cr