sumption 2:** Financial markets will provide positive, albeit volatile, returns over your investment horizon.\n    *   **Mitigation:** Using **SIPs** (Systematic Investment Plans) averages your purchase cost and mitigates timing risk. **Do not stop SIPs during market downturns; this is when you buy more units.**\n*   **Risk 1: Crypto Volatility.** The \u20b92,000 crypto allocation could lose significant value quickly.\n    *   **Mitigation:** This is a small, capped part of your portfolio. Never allocate goal-based money to crypto. Consider this money risk capital.\n*   **Risk 2: Underperformance of chosen funds.**\n    *   **Mitigation:** Invest in well-established, large fund houses with a long track record. For equity, prefer low-cost **Index Funds**. Review performance annually, not monthly.\n*   **Risk 3: Inflation.** The cost of the bike or phone might increase in 1-2 years.\n    *   **Mitigation:** Your monthly surplus is high enough to absorb a small cost overrun. The growth-oriented allocation for the bike fund is specifically designed to outpace inflation.\n\n---\n\n### **6) Immediate Action Checklist (Next 7 Days)**\n\n1.  [ ] **Open Demat & Trading Accounts:** If you don't have them, choose a reputable discount broker (e.g., Zerodha, Groww, Angel One) for stocks, ETFs, and mutual funds. For crypto, use a major Indian exchange (e.g., CoinDCX, WazirX).\n2.  [ ] **Complete KYC for Mutual Funds:** This is a one-time process through your broker or a platform like CoinSwitch Kuber, MFUtility, etc.\n3.  [ ] **Set Up Emergency Fund:** Transfer **\u20b948,000** (or start with whatever you have now and top up over two months) into a Liquid Fund or a separate bank account. Label it \"Emergency Fund\".\n4.  [ ] **Research & Select Funds:** Based on the recommendation, pick 1-2 specific funds for each category. Use resources like Value Research Online or Moneycontrol to compare funds.\n    *   *Example:*\n    *   *Arbitrage Fund: [e.g., Edelweiss Arbitrage Fund]*\n  